Name: epithelial and subepithelial dystrophy
Definition: A corneal dystrophy that primarily affects the corneal epithelium and its basement membrane.

Name: epithelial-stromal TGFBI dystrophy
Definition: A corneal dystrophy that is characterized by abnormal deposition of proteins in the cornea and is caused by mutations in TGFBI gene of chromosome 5q.

Name: stromal dystrophy
Definition: A corneal dystrophy that affects the corneal stroma.

Name: corneal endothelial dystrophy
Definition: A corneal dystrophy that affects the corneal endothelium and/or the descemet membrane.

Name: Chandler syndrome
Definition: A corneal dystrophy that is characterized by corneal edema
